headline: 'The unnatural alliance between Trump and White evangelicals has cost them dearly, even if it allowed them to gain positions of power'
description: Historian SÃ©bastien Fath discusses the history and dynamics of evangelical Protestant churches in an interview with Le Monde. Despite their current vibrancy, their growth is not inevitable, the researcher argues.

Iran says an 'unprecedented' deal is 'within reach' ahead of US talks
description: Iran's foreign minister issued a positive statement ahead of Thursday's scheduled talks in Geneva, expressing that Iran and the US have 'a historic opportunity to strike an unprecedented agreement.' Meanwhile, Donald Trump has carried out a massive military build-up in the Middle East aimed at pressuring Tehran into cutting a deal.

headline: Four years of war in Ukraine: Five photographers on assignment for Le Monde share their most striking images from 2025
description: Five photographers who covered the conflict in 2025 have each chosen an emblematic image of the conflict. These unique perspectives reveal, beyond the official figures and statements, the mark that this new year of war has left on them.

headline: Cristel, the high-end cookware specialist, to open a second production site
description: Defying the trend among many French manufacturers, this company based in Doubs, northeastern France, is facing soaring demand.

headline: Rekindled love: 'Something had happened and it split me in two. I had never experienced that before'
description: They met, fell in love and then parted ways. Life's twists and turns eventually brought them back together. Sylvain, 53, shares his story with Laurence, who is also 53.

description: After the army killed on Sunday the leader of Mexico's most powerful cartel, David Mora, a researcher at the International Crisis Group, expresses concern about the violence that could result from divisions within the criminal group and from the ambitions of rival cartels.

headline: EU plunged into uncertainty over US trade deal
description: The European Parliament suspended the ratification of the Turnberry agreement on Monday after the US Supreme Court struck down tariffs imposed by the Trump administration. But European imports now face a new tax introduced by the American president.

headline: Dark Bank: American suspected of leading an international criminal organization extradited to France
description: Huzefa Hafiz Ismail arrived on French soil on Friday. He was arrested in August 2024 in Texas at the request of French judicial authorities, who suspect him of leading a vast money laundering network.
